Location: Sweden




**We Are**
 RTB House is a global company that provides state-of-the-art marketing technologies for top brands and agencies worldwide. Its proprietary ad-buying engine is the first in the world to be power entirely by Deep Learning algorithms, enabling advertisers to generate outstanding results and reach their goals at every stage of the funnel.




 Our team in the Nordics consists of 15 people and is an integral part of our company’s global presence. We combine local expertise with our broader company vision. We embrace a "remote-first" approach, allowing our team members the flexibility to work remotely most of the time. However, to maintain a strong team dynamic and allow for valuable in-person interactions, we aim to meet regularly in our office in central Stockholm.




 The sales department in the Nordics is crucial in driving our company's success, working collaboratively to deliver top-notch digital advertising solutions with professionalism, integrity, and passion to boost our clients's businesses.




**Why RTB House?**
 If you are looking for a place where you can manage the entire sales cycle from prospecting to closing while working with major brands, handling senior client interactions, and participating in key industry events to contribute to the strategic market positioning in the Nordics, then RTB House might be the right fit for you.




**You Will**
* Handle the entire sales cycle from prospecting to closing to generate sales with some of the biggest e-commerce brands in the region;
* Directly engage with Directors and senior decision-makers on the client side;
* Collaborate with technical and account management teams to ensure campaign success;
* Contribute to strategy and growth as a digital market leader in the Nordic region;
* Develop strategies to meet client needs and acquire new business while reporting on sales process status for potential new customers;
* Maintain and elevate client relationships at all business levels;
* Participate in major industry events.


**Desired Experience**
* Years of seasoned experience in direct B2B sales in digital marketing or advertising, with demonstrated success in selling high-ticket, complex solutions to e-commerce and marketing teams at large corporations with a consultative selling approach;
* Extensive knowledge of e-commerce and online advertising, ideally paired with an existing network of key contacts and decision-makers in the industry;
* Demonstrated ability to forecast sales, build sales plans, and translate customer needs into profitable solutions while consistently hitting KPIs in mid to longer-term sales cycles;
* Strong analytical skills, self-motivation, entrepreneurial mindset, and positive achiever attitude;
* Excellent communication and presentation skills in Swedish and English (C1 or above), other Scandinavian languages are a plus;
* Recognized as a thought leader in online advertising, e-commerce and/or performance marketing industries, capable of building a vision with prospects and establishing effective relationships with key stakeholders up to C-level.


**We Offer**
* We prioritize flexible working arrangements in a hybrid set-up where you can decide for yourself if you want to regularly mingle with colleagues in our downtown Stockholm office near T-Centralen, work from the comfort of your home, or even work abroad from anywhere in the world for up to two months each year;
* We offer a top-of-the-market compensation package, consisting of an above-market-average base and an attractive bonus scheme;
* We provide a pension plan and accident insurance to support your future and well-being;
* You’re starting out with 28 vacation days - that can turn into 30 days after a 2-year tenure;
* You will have a structured and interactive onboarding, accompanied by a supporting team member assigned to guide you during your orientation phase to make sure you’re settling in with ease;
* An international working environment that inspires you and enables you to develop projects as part of a highly qualified cross-functional team;
* We care about your development and help you continuously grow your career with us as part of your personalized development plan - supported by a yearly training budget and subsidized language course.


**Apply now!**
 You don't need to tick every box to apply. If you are passionate about digital marketing, send us your CV, and we'll review it.

**Your Job Title:** 
 Manufacturing Engineer Electronics




**Job Location:** 
 Sweden - Danderyd (on-site)




****Purpose:****
 As a Manufacturing Engineer Electronics, you will play a crucial role in supporting our production lines and technicians. You will be responsible for ESD management, component fault analysis and repair, and overseeing the test run process. Your expertise will be vital in maintaining high standards of quality and efficiency in our production of electro-optical measurement systems for surveying, construction, and civil engineering. Your extensive knowledge and experience within electronics will be crucial in this role.




**Key Responsibilities**
* Provide technical support to production to ensure delivery reliability;
* Analyze and address deviations in products and equipment;
* Monitor and improve ergonomics in production;
* Drive process improvements and implement enhanced working methods;
* Identify, develop and plan preventive activities;
* Statistically monitor, measure, and analyze process quality;
* Maintain and calibrate production equipment;
* Maintain and update calibration and work instructions;
* Introduce change order processes and test series in production;
* Ensure quality information is disseminated to relevant managers;
* Participate in production and equipment reviews during the development process;
* Educate production personnel on equipment and methods;
* Analyze and resolve Defect Product Returns (DPRs);
* Support other departments with tests and investigations;
* Lead projects related to production equipment development.


**Competence Requirements**
* Extensive expertise in electronics, complemented by broad competence in areas such as mechanics, optics, production technology, project management, or quality work;
* Proficiency in MS Office and Google programs;
* Excellent knowledge of Swedish and English;
* Strong communication skills;
* Experience from CAD programs is an advantage.


****Why Join Us?****
 At Trimble Inc. we value innovation, collaboration, and continuous improvement. You will have the opportunity to work on exciting projects, lead initiatives, and contribute to the success of our production processes. We offer a supportive work environment, professional development opportunities, and a chance to make a real impact.




 Join us and be a part of our journey towards excellence in manufacturing!




**About Trimble**
 Dedicated to the world’s tomorrow, Trimble is a technology company delivering solutions that enable our customers to work in new ways to measure, build, grow and move goods for a better quality of life. Core technologies in positioning, modelling, connectivity and data analytics connect the digital and physical worlds to improve productivity, quality, safety, transparency and sustainability. From purpose-built products and enterprise lifecycle solutions to industry cloud services, Trimble is transforming critical industries such as construction, geospatial, agriculture and transportation to power an interconnected world of work. For more information about Trimble (NASDAQ: TRMB), visit:
 **www.trimble.com**
**Trimble’s Inclusiveness Commitment**
 We believe in celebrating our differences. That is why our diversity is our strength. To us, that means actively participating in opportunities to be inclusive. Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion have guided our current success while also moving our desire to improve. We actively seek to add members to our community who represent our customers and the places we live and work.




 We have programs in place to make sure our people are seen, heard, and welcomed and most importantly that they know they belong, no matter who they are or where they are coming from.




